Deutsche Bank Has Averted Fraud Attempts, Handelsblatt Reports

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-09-22T05:21:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/deutsche-bank-has-averted-fraud-attempts-handelsblatt-reports.html
Deutsche Bank AG (DBK)  has managed to
stop several attempts at fraudulent trading in the past few
years and is building a risk-management center in Berlin,
 Handelsblatt  reported, citing Chief Risk Officer Hugo Banziger.  The center will eventually have about 700 employees,
Banziger told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  